author: John S. Roberts
title: Liberal NJ Senator Makes MAJOR Announcement About Presidential Run in 2020…
text:
08:38pm January 21, 2017   
If Donald Trump accomplishes at least half of the things he’s promised (including lowering taxes and weakening ISIS), there’s a pretty decent chance he’ll win the Electoral College once again in 2020. 
What Democrats will probably do is run another Barack Obama-type. Meaning, a young, charismatic minority – either male or female. 
(Insert racist Republican joke here). 
Progressive New Jersey Sen. Cory Booker, thankfully, says he’s not thinking about a run for president in 2020. 
So, he’ll probably run. 
From Daily Caller : 
New Jersey Sen. Cory Booker said on Saturday that he will not run for president in 2020. 
“Four years will be here in a blink. Are you going to run for president?” CNN’s Brooke Baldwin asked Booker during an interview at the Women’s March in Washington, D.C. 
“No,” Booker said emphatically, “and I think we make a mistake…if we’re focused on four years from now.” 
“I will definitely be one of many in this country lifting our voice stepping out to fight, but we weaken ourselves if we think that this is about 2020.” 
… 
“So right now, I don’t care about 2020; I don’t care about 2018.” 
Okay, Cory. You’re on the record. 
You’re out. 
You won’t want to look like a hypocrite, now will you? LIKE this article?
